            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This is a problem with namespace packages.  When you get this kind of error, you'll find in your site-packages an extension which was installed at \"flaskext\" and not inside a directory that gets listed in a .pth file.  Namespace packages require a very specific `__init__.py`, which the broken installation at \"flaskext\" does not provide.\n\nWe discussed this issue upstream, but ultimately abandoned namespace packages, preferring flask_extension.py instead of flaskext/extension.py.  The full discussion is here:\n\nhttp://flask.pocoo.org/mailinglist/archive/2011/9/25/ann-migration-to-new-extension-distribution/\n\nThe workaround is to find the offending package installation, uninstall it, and reinstall it.  It's a bug somewhere in the packaging tools.  When most frustrated, I find a pure `python setup.py install` works.\n"
        },
